## BlankTab


**<u>Description</u>**: This extension opens a new blank tab.
**<u>How to Use</u>**:
1. Write a step: `BlankTab`.
2. `Switch to tab <x>`.
3. Replace <x> with the **id** of the tab. If you have 2 tabs, it will be 1. If you have 3 tabs, it will be 2, for 4 tabs, it will be 3 and so on.





### Details
- **Description:** Open a new blank tab
- **Inputs:** []
- **Resources:** []
- **Async:** false
- [Add to Production (Europe)](https://app.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=BlankTab&org=true&%3D%3D)
- [Add to Production (US)](https://app-us.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=BlankTab&org=true&%3D%3D)
- [Add to Free trial](https://app2.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=BlankTab&org=true&%3D%3D)
## Reload


**<u>Description</u>**:This extension reloads the current web page.

**<u>How to Use</u>**:
1. Write a step: `Reload`.
2. This will reload the active tab.





### Details
- **Description:** Reloads the active browser tab
- **Inputs:** []
- **Resources:** []
- **Async:** false

## StoreURL


**<u>Description</u>**: This extension stores the URL of the current browser tab.

**<u>How to Use</u>**:
1. Write a step: `StoreURL returning $currenturl`.
2. This will save the URL of the active tab into the variable **$currentURL**.




### Details
- **Description:** Stores the URL of the current browser tab
- **Inputs:** []
- **Resources:** []
- **Async:** false
- [Add to Production (Europe)](https://app.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=StoreURL&org=true&)
- [Add to Production (US)](https://app-us.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=StoreURL&org=true&)
- [Add to Free trial](https://app2.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=StoreURL&org=true&)
## localStorageGet


**<u>Description</u>**: This extension allows you to retrieve values stored into the local storage using the setLocalStorage extension or that are stored into local storage by the web application itself.

**<u>How to Use</u>**:
1. Write a step: `localStorageGet (key)` returning **$var**.
2. `key` in this case will be the key of the data stored in the **localStorageSet** extension e.g. authcode.




### Details
- **Description:** Retrieve data stored into the browser local storage
- **Inputs:** ["key"]
- **Resources:** []
- **Async:** false
- [Add to Production (Europe)](https://app.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=localStorageGet&org=true&%3D%3D)
- [Add to Production (US)](https://app-us.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=localStorageGet&org=true&%3D%3D)
- [Add to Free trial](https://app2.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=localStorageGet&org=true&%3D%3D)
## localStorageSet


**<u>Description</u>**: This extension allows you to pass in a value to store in the browser local storage.

**<u>How to Use</u>**:
1. Write a step: `localStorageSet (key, value)`.
2. `key` in this case will be the variable name e.g. authcode and `value` will be the value you want to store e.g. 475923




### Details
- **Description:** Store data into the browser local storage
- **Inputs:** ["key","value"]
- **Resources:** []
- **Async:** false
- [Add to Production (Europe)](https://app.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=localStorageSet&org=true&%3D%3D)
- [Add to Production (US)](https://app-us.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=localStorageSet&org=true&%3D%3D)
- [Add to Free trial](https://app2.virtuoso.qa/#/add-language-extension?name=localStorageSet&org=true&%3D%3D)
